    "question": "“Attribution is tough with multi-device journeys. Does AI unify that so I know if the same person who clicked on mobile also purchased on desktop?",
    "answer": "Attribution is indeed a challenge for marketers, especially in today's multi-device, multi-channel world. However, AI has proven to be a game-changer in this area by unifying customer data across devices and channels to provide a more comprehensive view of the customer journey.\n\nOne way AI can help with attribution is through the use of deterministic or probabilistic matching. Deterministic matching uses a unique identifier, such as a login or email address, to track a user's behavior across devices. This allows marketers to accurately attribute a conversion to a specific customer, even if they switch devices. On the other hand, probabilistic matching uses machine learning algorithms to analyze patterns and behaviors to make educated guesses about which devices belong to the same user. While not as accurate as deterministic matching, it can still provide valuable insights for attribution.\n\nThere are also AI-powered attribution platforms, such as AdRoll, that use advanced algorithms to analyze customer data and attribute conversions to specific touchpoints. These platforms can also help identify cross-device and cross-channel patterns, allowing marketers to optimize their campaigns accordingly.\n\nFor actionable advice, I would recommend that marketers start by implementing a cross-device tracking system, whether through deterministic matching or an attribution platform. This will provide a more accurate view of the customer journey and help with attribution. Additionally, regularly analyzing data and adjusting attribution models based on insights from AI can help improve accuracy over time.\n\nOverall, AI has greatly improved attribution capabilities for marketers and continues to evolve and improve as technology advances. By leveraging AI tools and strategies, marketers can gain a better understanding of their customers' behaviors and optimize their campaigns for maximum impact.",
